[This past week seems to have been a quiet week for polio with no newly confirmed cases of either WPV or cVDPV. There also seems to be a decrease in environmental samples with only Pakistan having positive environmental samples for the WPV1 circulating in the region. The not-so-good news is that while there were only 4 positive samples, there was 1 from each of the 4 provinces, so the virus is still in circulation in all 4 provinces of the country.

For a map showing the locations of cases of WPV and cVDPV, see http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

